text: Hesperonatalius is a genus of Australian mygalomorph spiders in the family Anamidae, first described by M. A. Castalanelli, J. A. Huey, M. J. Hillyer & Mark Stephen Harvey in 2017. it contains only three species. ==References== ==External links== Category:Mygalomorphae genera Category:Anamidae
title: Hesperonatalius
